Design patterns standards

Scope
* Applies to design patterns examples and modules
* Extends dotnet rules

Principles
* Follow SOLID principles
* Favor composition over inheritance except where patterns require otherwise
* Keep responsibilities single and well named

Pattern implementation
* Implement patterns faithfully with clear intent
* Provide minimal yet sufficient examples that compile
* Avoid global mutable state
* Ensure thread safety where patterns are used in concurrent contexts

Documentation
* Document the intent context and consequences of each pattern
* Include usage guidance and tradeoffs

Testing
* Provide small usage examples that can be executed
* Validate expected behavior and edge conditions

